snippet.textDisplay: I don’t know a whole lot about the condition she has, but it certainly seems as if something very traumatic happened that caused her to need multiple voices/personalities.  You can see when she gets emotional that the stronger part of her takes over. And you can see her trying to focus on what one voice is saying in her mind and to speak coherently. I wonder if the therapy that can help people with dissociative identity disorder integrate might be useful?  On another note - my heart just breaks for her struggle. I wish her mom or therapist held her hand and sat closer to her.

snippet.textDisplay: As if she couldn't've been more relatable. I loved her as the girl in school that was smart, into her image and fun to be around, but will set you straight. I adore her as a woman that battles mental health, denied it for some time, and had relationships that were further damaging to her already fragile state. I currently know the feeling of being left out of things that molded a major place in my past because of me health. My mom battles schizophrenic episodes and we both have bipolar disorder. She was misdiagnosed for a long time, and as a result, we were shunned from the family. I was involved in promoting and marketing for musicians in Memphis and when I had an episode, I was removed. The anniversary of a show I helped start went on without me, without recognition of my contributions. It Hurts to be ill and alone, without support or understanding. I'm happy she set the record straight, and I do not think the reboot should include Lark in every episode, but a cameo on occasion to honor her legacy and contribution would be respectful, and an invite to dinner would've been nice, if they Truly loved her

snippet.textDisplay: There's nothing wrong with Lark that's not wrong with anyone else. It's all in  how we perceive betrayal, heartbreak and downfalls. We all hurt and can become embarrassed over numerous bad things that transpires throughout life. However, it is all in how we process it. For her to have been a big star and perhaps "fall off" can be devastating which can cause major bouts of depression for years to come. Being wealthy and then becoming broke overnight and shunned by those that are supposed be there for you when you fall and not kick you when down, can really really hurt deep inside. I know this 1st hand. However,  my advice to her would be only God can judge you and you are born alone and you shall die alone in this cruel world we all share. Don't worry yourself with how others perceive and treat you anymore. You are still gorgeous and you only need God. Believe in God and God alone. Have faith in him and know that all things are meant to be, rather good or bad. God works in mysterious ways. Sometimes he'll let you fall off to rid you of those around you that prey on you and use you. Once they're gone from your life he'll restore you to who you truly are. A blessed and true child of God. ❤
